sect1.para:
An image consists of:



a kernel;

an initrd, which is basically a collection of unpacked udebs;

in some cases a boot loader and/or configuration files used for booting.

sect3.para:
The pkg-list script will also look for the presence of files named common and local and thus pkg-lists/netboot/common is processed next. This file exists and lists a number of udebs that belong in any netboot image, independent of the architecture. This file also contains two include directives:


#include "base"
#include "kernel"
